article.headline: Jacksonville St. 78, SE Missouri 72
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Seniors Courtney Bradley, Nick Smith and Harold Crow combined for 62 points to lead Jacksonville State to a 78-72 win over Southeast Missouri Saturday night. Bradley scored 28 points with 10 rebounds and Nick Smith added a career-high 24 points. Crow followed with 10 in the Gamecocks' (9-21, 7-13 Ohio Valley Conference) season sweep of the Redhawks (11-19, 9-11 OVC). It was Senior Night for Jacksonville State, which entered the night needing a win and losses by Eastern Illinois and Morehead State in order to earn the eighth seed in the league tournament. Samford handed EIU a defeat, but Morehead State went to Clarksville, Tenn., and downed the league champion to earn the bid. In a game that was tied 13 times and saw the lead change hands 15 times, the Gamecocks shot 48 percent from the floor and 38 percent from 3-point range to pull out the win. The Redhawks were led by Dionte Perry, who had a double-double with 18 points and 10 rebounds. Brandon Foust had a team-high 21 points and Terrick Willoughby added 11 points.
